snippet.textDisplay: I do like with makeup geek that if you use both their eye and face shades, you're less likely to create waste. If a shade goes bad, you can just chuck that small tin rather than throwing out a whole palette. You can add in your face products, and replace individual shades as needed with minimal packaging being tossed. I have far too much makeup at the moment to even consider purchasing any makeup for 2020, but when I do start to use up my current hoard I will be purchasing from brands like makeupgeek, colour pop, Elate Cosmetics etc--basically any brand that will allow me to just buy a single bronzer or single eyeshadow and Chuck it into my magnetic palettea

snippet.textDisplay: Unrelated to this video, but since it's the most recent- I'm new to your channel and you've already helped me in my life. It may seem superficial but is not-- I've always been a musician and gone to concerts, but I was with my ex for 10 years, my whole adult life, and then not anymore.
